Here’s a TekAutomate Steps UI flow for your MSO4/5/6 Series scope that saves the setup to C:/setups/test.set and takes a screenshot.

```json
{
  "steps": [
    {
      "type": "connect",
      "label": "Connect to Scope",
      "params": {
        "instrumentIds": [],
        "printIdn": true
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "write",
      "label": "Save Setup to C:/setups/test.set",
      "params": {
        "command": "SAVE:SETUP \"C:/setups/test.set\""
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "save_screenshot",
      "label": "Save Screenshot",
      "params": {
        "filename": "capture.png",
        "scopeType": "modern",
        "method": "pc_transfer"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "disconnect",
      "label": "Disconnect from Scope",
      "params": {
        "instrumentIds": []
      }
    }
  ]
}
```

This flow will:
1. Connect to the scope.
2. Save the setup file to the specified path.
3. Capture a screenshot and transfer it to the PC as capture.png.
4. Disconnect from the scope.

